translated: Jäderberg, Karl Elis, district medical officer, Alingsås, born on August 6th, 1891 in Guldsmedshyttan, Örebro County, the son of the estate manager Erik J. and Anna Rosell. Married on August 22nd to dentist Dagmar Uppvall. Children: Bengt-Elis, born in 1925. Passed high school exam in Örebro in 1910, achieved Bachelor of Medicine degree in Uppsala in 1917, achieved Medical Licentiate degree in Stockholm in 1922. Temporary assistant doctor at Allmänna BB in Stockholm from 1919-1920, temporary assistant city physician in Söderhamn in 1920, temporary district physician and assistant physician at Karlshamns hospital for seven months in 1921-1923. Temporary city physician in Skellefteå and district physician in Sotenäs in 1922, temporary district physician in Dorotea in 1923, then district physician in Ryds district from 1923-1924, temporary district physician there from 1924-1925 and district physician from 1925-1942, and district medical officer in Alingsås district from 1942. Worked as a doctor at Ryd's spa and bath-house from 1924-1929, and as a railway physician for Karlshamn-Vislanda-Bolmens Railway from 1923-1942 and Hönshylte-Kvarnamåla railway from 1925-1942. Was vice chairman of the health committee, member of municipal council, and chairman of the temperance committee in Ryd. Awarded with RNO.
